		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Woot! Thanks infiniteneslives!<br /><br />I played through Final Fantasy 4, 5, and 6 with my wife, all of which have 2 player modes. 5 and 6 allow you to assign characters to controllers---but 4 basically makes both controllers act as one, just like the above adapter does. It wasn't too hard to agree on which characters were &quot;ours&quot; at any given time and remember to let the other player use the RPG menu at the appropriate time, so I figured, if I had an adapter like this we could play ANY rpg in the same &quot;tandem&quot; fashion. Could just pass the controller back and forth, but there's a psychological component of really sharing the game with somebody when they can be a copilot with their own controller.<br /><br />Probably wouldn't work for anything but RPGs but, looking forward to it anyway <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />

		

